<section class="stack">
  <div class="panel">
    <p class="eyebrow">License</p>
    <h1>Customer access and offline license setup</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      The sample app is public, but running it requires private gem access and
      signed offline license variables for both gems.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="grid">
    <article class="tile">
      <h3>Package access</h3>
      <p>Configure Bundler with GitHub Packages credentials.</p>
      <pre><code>bundle config set --local https://rubygems.pkg.github.com/kanutocd USER:TOKEN

or configure credentials system wide:

bundle config https://rubygems.pkg.github.com/kanutocd USER:TOKEN</code></pre>
    </article>

    <article class="tile">
      <h3>License env</h3>
      <pre><code>CDC_REDIS_PRO_LICENSE_KEY
CDC_REDIS_PRO_LICENSE_PUBLIC_KEY
CDC_ORCHESTRATOR_PRO_LICENSE_KEY
CDC_ORCHESTRATOR_PRO_LICENSE_PUBLIC_KEY</code></pre>
    </article>

    <article class="tile">
      <h3>Install flow</h3>
      <pre><code>bundle install
bundle exec rake docs:generate</code></pre>
    </article>

    <article class="tile">
      <h3>Customer handoff</h3>
      <p>Use the private gem access token and offline license file together.</p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>
